response.description: Schedule K-1 (Form 1065): Partner’s Share of Income, Deductions, Credits, etc.” — is a U.S. tax document used to report each partner’s share of a partnership’s earnings, losses, deductions, and credits.

Item D.description: Check this box if your partnership is a publicly traded partnership (PTP)...

Item E.description: Partner’s Taxpayer Identification Number (TIN)—which can be either your SSN, ITIN, or EIN.

Item F.description: Partner’s contact information and whether you’re a foreign or domestic partner.

Item G.description: Partner is a general partner or limited partner?

Item H.description: Partner is a foreign or domestic partner?

Item J.description: Share of the partnership’s profits, loss, and capital...
Item J.group: Part 3 - Partner’s Share of Current Year Income, Deductions, Credits, and Other Items

Item K.description: Share of the partnership’s liabilities (recourse, qualified nonrecourse, and recourse).
Item K.group: Part 3 - Partner’s Share of Current Year Income, Deductions, Credits, and Other Items

Item L.description: Capital account changes during the year.
Item L.group: Part 3 - Partner’s Share of Current Year Income, Deductions, Credits, and Other Items

Item M.description: Check 'yes' if you contributed property with a built-in gain or loss.
Item M.group: Part 3 - Partner’s Share of Current Year Income, Deductions, Credits, and Other Items

Item n.description: Partner’s Share of Net Unrecognized Section 704(c) Gain or (Loss).
Item n.group: Part 3 - Partner’s Share of Current Year Income, Deductions, Credits, and Other Items
